        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em>Whistling, you call forth heavy snowfall for a moment in an area, pelting creatures with snow.</em></p><p><strong>Dexterity Save</strong> </p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 1d6 bludgeoning]] damage and [[/damage 1d6 cold]] damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Area Hazard:</strong> The area is covered with snow and counts as &amp;reference[difficult terrain]. This difficult terrain is removed if any amount of it comes into contact with rain or fire damage.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> The radius of the spell increases by 10 ft. for each spell level above 1st level.</p>",
            "chat": "<strong>Dexterity Save</strong> </p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 1d6 bludgeoning]] damage and [[/damage 1d6 cold]] damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Area Hazard:</strong> The area is covered with snow and counts as &amp;reference[difficult terrain]. This difficult terrain is removed if any amount of it comes into contact with rain or fire damage.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> The radius of the spell increases by 10 ft. for each spell level above 1st level.</p>"
